Description: 
    Deploys basic analysis chapters for the "Orchestrating Single Cell Analysis with Bioconductor" book.
    This describes the early steps of a typical single-cell RNA-seq analysis, ranging from quality control,
    normalization, various forms of dimensionality reduction, clustering and detection of marker genes.
